values: So I'm in my class, having finished my candy; in that moment you just ate a whole lot of sugar, waiting for that moment of hyperness...Well it's valentine's day, you should eat as much candy as you can, righ? Ofcourse you'll have to be in charge of your self whenever you get hyper and feel like doing weird things. Like I said, that moment waiting for the bust just went by anfd now im very hyper; hopefully I'll be able to mantain my self from doing weird crazy stuff. There hasn't been many things going on lately just the normal, so I pretty much don't h ave much to talk about except to tell some story.

The word hero dosen't mean that you NEED to have special powers. It could mean that you believe in someone greatly and that you show respect towards them. Many children consider thir parents as their heroes, teen agers consider their friends as heroes even parents consider their children as heroes. I personally dont have a hero although I still look up at people that have done something important.

There are many thing I'm not perfect in but I work still work on them to make them be better, like drawing. I like to draw and I'm good at it but I still need work to become better in details. I'm also not so good at math but I try my best to understand it although I don't practice that often.

There was one time when I felt disapointed because I promised my dad that I would spent the weekend with him.That day my mom and me had moved to our new home, and she wanted me to spend the first night with her at our new home.That day when I went to the store my dad was sitting there having a drink with one of his friends, he asked me if I was going to spend the weekend with him as I did all the time.I said that there wasn't a problem and that he could pick me up at what ever time he could.At about ten in the night he came for me.He was drunk.Him and my mom got in a figh, for I felt very bad because I created that fight, and because I promised my dad something that I didn't keep.
